<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1146">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/70b.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Repeat to Vice Consul of the Netherlands, Tampico, following telegram
                            from the Netherlands Minister at Washington: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Conform yourself following telegram sent today by Secretary of
                                    State to American Consul saying: [Quotes telegram to Consul
                                    Canada, May 20, 1914.]</p>
                                <p rend="right">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rappard</hi>.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>